message: On saturday I saw a bunch of parrots fly over my house in Lower Pac Heights. Noisy.
Anyway, later on that day I went up Telegraph Hill and saw the parrots there and saw the were the same breed (looked the same and made the same obnoxious noise)
You think these are the same ones? How far do they fly around?
Oh ok, so they get around a lot. Cool!
yeah, my neighbor (in Nob Hill) feeds those darn parrots every morning at 7am.  it was neat for the first few days and I got some great shots of them, but it's terribly annoying these days.
I've seen them fly over Dolores Park a couple times and once around Potrero Hill...
also, check out neflix streaming for a documentary
I read it's illegal to feed them?

"A controversial San Francisco city ordinance passed on June 5, 2007, prohibits the feeding of parrots in public spaces. The feeding ban was championed by Mark Bittner, the birds' most outspoken supporter who fed them for years and wrote the book The Wild Parrots of Telegraph Hill. Other local conservationists also supported the ban, though some residents continue to object.[6]" Public spaces though, so maybe not out of your window...
